  <summary>5/21/1998--Introduced.
Declares that the House of Representatives: (1) condemns child labor exploitation wherever it occurs in the United States and overseas; (2) endorses and supports the Global March Against Child Labor; and (3) pledges to work for effective international action to eradicate the worst forms of child labor by the year 2000.</summary>
